HEADWORD: Noctivagant
<hw>Noc*tiv"a*gant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nox</ets>, <ets>noctis</ets>, night + <ets>vagans</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>vagari</ets> to wander about.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Going
about in the night; night-wandering.</def>⟦br⟧
